SIMPLE: incorrect
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incorrect
<hw>In`cor*rect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incorrectus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>incorrect</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Correct</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not correct; not according to a copy or model, or to
established rules; inaccurate; faulty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The piece, you think, is <qex>incorrect</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not in accordance with the truth; inaccurate; not
exact; <as>as, an <ex>incorrect</ex> statement or
calculation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not accordant with duty or morality; not duly
regulated or subordinated; unbecoming; improper; <as>as,
<ex>incorrect</ex> conduct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It shows a will most <qex>incorrect</qex> to heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wit of the last age was yet more <qex>incorrect</qex> than
their language.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inaccurate; erroneous; wrong; faulty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorrection</ent>⟦br⟧
